<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><author>Francesco Testa</author>
<hymn_number>3362</hymn_number>
<lyrics>[V1]
 Let the thirsty and burdened come to me
 Let my children come
 I will break these yokes of slavery
 Children you'll take mine
 I've been through the fire of death for you
 I did overcome
 For death has no power over me
 I'm the of life
 My child I long to be with you
 So I can fill the emptiness within you
 All I ask of you is to receive
 And please realize, and please realize
 The cross was meant for you
 There were people laughing at the cross
 And I wept for them
 Please forgive them father they don't know
 I cried in my pain
 You too come and take a look at me
 A look at the cross
 Is it really so hard to receive
 More than you deserve?
 You too my friend come close to the cross
 I'll let you decide
 You can either kneel or tum
 Please choose to be saved
 My Lord I long to be with you
 I'm sorry I've been so blind
 I did not realize
 But then your spirit touched my heart
 And on he sang
 And the revealed
 That the cross was meant for me
 Your cross was meant for me
 Your death was meant for me
 Your blood was meant for me
 Give me life
 According to your richness
 Give me life
 According to your will
 Give me life
 According to your goodness
 Give me life
 According to your love</lyrics>
<title>The cross was meant for you</title>
</song>